</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,259,1294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,483,439,466]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,477,439,466]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head broad, flat dome-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[846,930,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–88" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[173,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 87–88. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 87, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 88, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825603/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal area convex, frons rounded. Marginal carina broad, narrowed near 
<emphasis box="[776,832,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">dsms</emphasis>
, interrupted submedianly. Dorsal preantennal suture reaches 
<emphasis box="[243,299,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">dsms</emphasis>
but not 
<emphasis box="[393,432,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">ads</emphasis>
or lateral head margin, and does not separate dorsal anterior plate posteriorly. Dorsal anterior plate with transverse posterior thickening. Ventral anterior plate roughly crescent-shaped. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[180,263,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–88" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,193,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-23@40.[173,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 87–88. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 87, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 88, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825603/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi large, bulging. Pre- and postocular nodi of about equal size. Marginal temporal carina slender, of roughly even width. Gular plate with slightly concave lateral margins converging to median point. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[556,684,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–86" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,299,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-65@39.[151,1437,273,1865]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 85–86. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta. 85, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 86, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825601/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs 85–86</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis box="[696,721,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">ps</emphasis>
absent on abdominal segment III in both sexes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,259,1294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,691,718]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[725,806,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–86" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,299,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-65@39.[151,1437,273,1865]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 85–86. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta. 85, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 86, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825601/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
. Basal apodeme with rounded proximal end, and concave lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[336,422,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome with antero-lateral extensions, proximal margin straight to slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[257,340,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
). Mesosomal lobes bulging slightly. Ventral sclerite as in 
<figureCitation box="[972,1053,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
. Gonopore with several prominent extensions along proximal margin. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[718,792,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[858,1001,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–106" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1765,1789]" captionTargetBox="[285,1304,194,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-23@46.[269,1318,181,1741]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 95–106. Male genitalia. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua: 95, dorsal view. 96, male mesosome, ventral view. 97, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta: 98, dorsal view. 99, male mesosome, ventral view. 100, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus ethologus laetus: 101, dorsal view. 102, male mesosome, ventral view. 103, male paramere, ventral view. Guimaraesiella (Malardifax) pandolura Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2017, ex Pericrocotus roseus stanfordi: 104, dorsal view. 105, male mesosome, ventral view. 106, male paramere, ventral view.Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825611/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Figs 98, 100</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[1240,1324,799,825]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,259,1294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,835,862]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[763,845,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–86" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[177,1418,299,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-65@39.[151,1437,273,1865]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 85–86. Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta. 85, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 86, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825601/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
. Subgenital plate rounded trapezoidal, broad distally, with broad lateral submarginal bulges (
<figureCitation box="[589,673,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–90" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,205,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-17@41.[295,1292,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 89–90. Female subgenital plates and vulval margins. 89, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) sphagmotica n. sp. ex Coracina caeruleogrisea strenua. 90, Guimaraesiella (Guimaraesiella) nouankaoensis n. sp. ex Coracina caledonica seiuncta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825605/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
). Vulval margin gently rounded to somewhat flattened, with 2 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[239,283,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">vms</emphasis>
and 1–3 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[570,604,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 3–4 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[968,1005,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 1 
<emphasis box="[172,209,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">vos</emphasis>
near 
<emphasis box="[272,306,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">vss</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[549,633,943,969]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
