<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1437,259,1294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1195,1221]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</emphasis>
The single female from 
<emphasis box="[596,736,1195,1222]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">C. c. thilenii</emphasis>
is larger in all measurements than females from the type host (
<tableCitation box="[159,244,1231,1257]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Table 1</tableCitation>
), but is otherwise morphologically similar. We tentatively consider this specimen to be conspecific with female 
<typeStatus box="[234,344,1268,1294]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">paratypes</typeStatus>
, but more material is needed to confirm its true identity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
